The paper deals with duality theorems in logic, specifically for structures that interpret bunched logics. This involves techniques from modal, substructural, and categorical logic, which are all relevant to the areas of logic and theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses propositional connectives, which falls under the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper deals with De Morgan BI and Concurrent Separation Logic, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity), respectively. Finally, the paper contextualizes the "resource semantics" interpretation underpinning Separation Logic, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
